{"search_data": "OdishaAbadan Scheme to be Launched Soon in Odisha for Senior CitizenHighlights of Odisha Abadan SchemeTo make the scheme accessible to all senior citizens government is considering on some provision which are give belowIn the first year of scheme, all the stakeholder will create awareness about the rights of Senior citizens and various other services.The government will spent as Rs 2.4 crore (Rs 8 lakh per district) for effective implementation of scheme.A \u201csenior citizens week\u201d will be organised at district-level to connect senior citizens with stakeholders.SSEPD will also cooperate with Bramhakumaris in schools and college to undertake awareness program regarding respect for elder people.AN open complaint management system regarding grievances of senior citizen will also open at district level.The complaints regarding elder citizen will be handled by two counselors or experts at district headquarters.Under the Abadan Scheme, the government is going to engage volunteers at local bus stands including cities of Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, Berhampur, Sambalpur and Rourkela where they will guide senior citizens about availability of seats in government and private buses. Those volunteers who are working on bus stand and guiding the senior citizen about the seats in bus would be receiving Rs. 3,000 per month from the government.The Abadan scheme is not launched yet, hence complete information would be available only after the scheme is officially launched by the Odisha Government.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}